# Local neutrality denylist — COPY this to `.githooks/neutrality.local`
# (that filename is git-ignored via `*.local`, so it never gets committed).
#
# One term per line. Each is matched case-insensitively (grep -iE) against the
# ADDED lines of any commit/push. Put here the COMPANY-SPECIFIC strings that
# must never reach git: company name, internal domains, real Jira project keys,
# product/customer names. These live only on your machine.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. Terms are regexes.
#
# Examples (replace with your real ones in neutrality.local, NOT here):
#   acme-corp
#   acme\.internal
#   \bACME\b
#   \b[A-Z]{3}-[0-9]+\b      # your real Jira project key prefix
#   some-internal-product-name
